---
import PlayerLayout from "../../layouts/PlayerLayout.astro";

const name = "Anthony Davis";
const team = "Dallas Mavericks";
const position = "Center/Forward";
---

<PlayerLayout {name} {team} {position}>
  <p>
    Anthony Davis is a two-way big who anchors the paint defensively and
    provides efficient scoring inside the arc. At his best, he’s a franchise-level
    rim protector and interior finisher who shifts a team’s ceiling on both ends.
  </p>

  <h2>Defensive impact</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Rim protection with length, timing, and verticality.</li>
    <li>Ability to switch onto guards in late-clock situations.</li>
    <li>Strong defensive rebounding to finish possessions.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Offensive role</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Primary roll man in pick-and-roll actions.</li>
    <li>Short-roll midrange and playmaking when traps come.</li>
    <li>Post-ups and duck-ins against mismatches or smaller lineups.</li>
  </ul>
</PlayerLayout>
